The first calling convention will only modify the names of the index and/or the names of the Index object that is the columns. In this case, the parameter
is ignored.

The second calling convention will modify the names of the corresponding index if mapper is a list or a scalar. However, if mapper is dict-like or a function, it will use the deprecated behavior of modifying the axis
